p:
9. Thus far: three possible meanings of “appearance.” These three meanings must be kept distinct:
appearance-1: a genuine appearance: a true phenomenon, something that appears directly and as itself;
• appearance-2: a false or specious appearance: a mere semblance, something that appears as what it is not;
• appearance-3: an appearance through which something else appears indirectly while remaining hidden, i.e., not appearing on its own.
